0xAB7F7241// AddConvarChangeListener
int ADD_CONVAR_CHANGE_LISTENER(char* conVarFilter, func handler);Parameters:conVarFilter: The Console Variable to listen for, this can be a pattern like "test:*", or null for anyhandler: The handler function.Returns: A cookie to remove the change handler.Adds a listener for Console Variable changes.The function called expects to match the following signature:function ConVarChangeListener(conVarName: string, reserved: any);conVarName: The ConVar that changed.reserved: Currently unused.Examples:JavaScript// listen for all convar changes
AddConvarChangeListener(null, (conVarName, reserved) => {
    print(GetConvarInt(conVarName))
})

// listen to convars that start with "script:"
AddConvarChangeListener("script:*", (conVarName, reserved) => {
    print(GetConvarInt(conVarName))
})

